Pumpkin Waffles - gf
  --Jessica Kellgren-Fozard

350g almond flour
175g pumpkin puree
15g powdered splenda
2 medium eggs
1/2 tsp baking powder
1 tsp vanilla
1/2 tsp cinnamon
1/2 tsp ginger
1/4 tsp salt

Heat the waffle iron and grease if necessary. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Dollop batter into iron (~1/4 c or 60g per waffle). Cook for 7 min.


Notes: If you use coconut flour instead of almond flour, reduce the amount. If you use sugar instead of splenda, use more (10x), or can make without any added sweetener.
